<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-565-254  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 565 254.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  June 11 1990 v11 n24 p38(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NASA planning free-flying service stations.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Puttre, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>NASA awarded two contracts in late May 1990 for studying thefeasibility of launching unmanned, free-flying satellite servicestations.andP;  The contracts for the Satellite Servicer System (SSS)were won by TRW Inc's Space andamp; Technology Group and Martin MariettaCorp's Space Systems division.andP;  The SSS workhorse will be TRW's19,000-lb Orbital Maneuvering Vehicle (OMV).andP;  One of the mainobjectives of the program is to perfect automated dockingprocedures.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   TRW Space and Technology Group (contracts)Martin Marietta Corp. Space Systems Co. (contracts).andO;Topic:     Government ContractsSatellitesMaintenanceUnited States. National Aeronautics and Space Administration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>